## 3. Inner loop — rate control (PID)

![Inner loop — rate control (PID)](multicopterControl_2026-05-14_inner.svg)

**Forward path** (`RateControl::update()`, `rate_control.cpp:71-86`):

```
   ω_sp ─►(Σ)─► e_ω ─┬─►[K·P]──┐
            ▲(−)     │          │
            │        └─►[K·I·i_f /s]─►(Σ_τ)─► τ
            │                          │
   ω        │      α ─►[-K·D] ─────────┤
   (gyro)   │                          │
            │      ω_sp ─►[FF] ────────┘
            │
   feedback from gyro
```

**Math, per axis** i ∈ {x, y, z}:

```
e_ω[i] = ω_sp[i] − ω[i]
τ[i]   = K[i] · ( P[i]·e_ω[i]  +  ∫_i  −  D[i]·α[i] )  +  FF[i]·ω_sp[i]
∫_i   ← clip( ∫_i + i_f·K[i]·I[i]·e_ω[i]·dt, ±lim_int[i] )    if !landed
i_f   = max(0, 1 − (e_ω[i] / 400°)²)                          ← nonlinear I-gain reducer
```

**Feedback paths shown in the diagram:**

- **Red** ($\omega$): primary rate feedback. Enters the negative input of the input summing junction (forms $e_\omega = \omega_{sp} - \omega$).
- **Blue** ($\alpha$): auxiliary feedback into the $-D$ block, from the gyro derivative `vehicle_angular_velocity.xyz_derivative`.

Note: The D term acts on **measured angular acceleration**, not on the time-derivative of the rate error. The integrator updates only when `!landed`, and saturation flags from `control_allocator_status` are written but the anti-windup gate inside `rate_control.cpp:92-99` is **commented out**.

**Per-channel parameters:**

| | **Roll (x)** | **Pitch (y)** | **Yaw (z)** |
|---|---|---|---|
| Setpoint source | `vehicle_rates_setpoint.roll` | `.pitch` | `.yaw` |
| **P** | `MC_ROLLRATE_P` = 0.15 | `MC_PITCHRATE_P` = 0.15 | `MC_YAWRATE_P` = 0.2 |
| **I** | `MC_ROLLRATE_I` = 0.2 | `MC_PITCHRATE_I` = 0.2 | `MC_YAWRATE_I` = 0.1 |
| **D** | `MC_ROLLRATE_D` = 0.003 | `MC_PITCHRATE_D` = 0.003 | `MC_YAWRATE_D` = 0.0 |
| **FF** | `MC_ROLLRATE_FF` = 0.0 | `MC_PITCHRATE_FF` = 0.0 | `MC_YAWRATE_FF` = 0.0 |
| **K** | `MC_ROLLRATE_K` = 1.0 | `MC_PITCHRATE_K` = 1.0 | `MC_YAWRATE_K` = 1.0 |
| Int. clip | `MC_RR_INT_LIM` = 0.30 | `MC_PR_INT_LIM` = 0.30 | `MC_YR_INT_LIM` = 0.30 |
| Output | `vehicle_torque_setpoint.xyz[0]` | `.xyz[1]` | `.xyz[2]` |

